Sample_treatment_protocol_ch1: BT12 cells were treated with 100nM mithramycin for 8-hours or 18-hours continous treatment then collected.
Sample_growth_protocol_ch1: BT12 cells were grown in RPMI-1640 medium (Invitrogen) supplemented with 10% fetal bovine serum (Gemini Bio-Products), 2 mM L-glutamine (Invitrogen), 100 U/mL penicillin and 100 μg/mL streptomycin (Invitrogen). Cell lines were maintained at less than 80% confluency at 37°C and 5% CO2 and confirmed to be mycoplasma negative every 6-months.
Sample_extract_protocol_ch1: ATAC-seq samples were extracted as described in Corces et al., Nature Methods, 2017., ATAC-seq libraries were prepared as described in Buenrostro et al., Corces et al., Nature Methods, 2017 with the addition of lambda phage and phiX spike-ins.
Sample_data_processing: Libraries were sequenced using 2x75 bp sequencing on the Illumina NextSeq 500 platform at the Van Andel Research Institute.  Data were demultplexed using bcl2fastq v2.20.0.
Supplementary_files_format_and_content: Bigwig files for raw and lambda corrected (lambda_corrected) peaks from all samples.
